    "# Chemical Process Monitoring Time-Series Dataset  \n",
    "## Notebook 2: Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Project Context\n",
    "This project investigates a chemical process monitoring dataset containing time-series sensor readings from multiple reactors operating under different regimes. The broader objective is to develop an intelligent monitoring framework for:\n",
    "\n",
    "- fault detection\n",
    "- predictive maintenance\n",
    "- process performance analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "In Notebook 1, the focus was on **data understanding**. That phase established that:\n",
    "\n",
    "- faults are rare and highly imbalanced\n",
    "- reactor and regime coverage are balanced\n",
    "- the dataset has a strong time-series structure\n",
    "- process variables are stable and tightly controlled\n",
    "- faults are likely subtle and context-dependent\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Purpose of This Notebook\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook performs a deeper **exploratory data analysis (EDA)** to uncover patterns that will guide feature engineering and modeling.\n",
    "\n",
    "Specifically, this notebook aims to:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Compare **normal vs faulty operating behavior**\n",
    "2. Examine **sensor distributions and shifts**\n",
    "3. Analyze **relationships between variables**\n",
    "4. Explore **fault behavior across regimes and reactors**\n",
    "5. Investigate **time-series trends and potential early warning signals**\n",
    "6. Generate insights for the next stage: **feature engineering**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why This Stage Matters\n",
    "\n",
    "In industrial systems, faults rarely appear as obvious extreme events. Instead, they often emerge as:\n",
    "\n",
    "- subtle shifts in process variables\n",
    "- deviations from stable operating ranges\n",
    "- patterns that evolve gradually over time\n",
    "\n",
    "This means exploratory analysis is essential for identifying which variables, relationships, and time dynamics are most informative for detecting faults."
   ]
  },
