    "- slight shifts in peak locations  \n",
    "- wider spread in faulty distributions  \n",
    "- heavier tails (especially in vibration and conversion rate)  \n",
    "\n",
    "This indicates that faults do not produce extreme outliers, but rather **subtle deviations from normal behavior**.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 2. Increased Variability Under Fault Conditions\n",
    "Variables such as:\n",
    "\n",
    "- `reactor_temp`\n",
    "- `reactor_pressure`\n",
    "- `vibration_rms`\n",
    "\n",
    "show broader distributions under fault conditions. This suggests that faults introduce **instability into the system**, causing:\n",
    "\n",
    "- increased fluctuations  \n",
    "- reduced process control consistency  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 3. Strong Overlap in Efficiency Metrics\n",
    "Key performance variables such as:\n",
    "\n",
    "- `selectivity`\n",
    "- `yield_pct`\n",
    "- `power_consumption_kw`\n",
    "\n",
    "show almost identical distributions between normal and faulty operation.\n",
    "\n",
    "This implies:\n",
    "\n",
    "- faults do not immediately impact final product quality  \n",
    "- the system remains efficient even when underlying issues are present  \n",
    "- these variables alone are **weak predictors of faults**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 4. Conversion Rate Shows Early Warning Signals\n",
    "The `conversion_rate` distribution shows:\n",
    "\n",
    "- a slight left tail under faults  \n",
    "- more spread compared to normal  \n",
    "\n",
    "This suggests that faults may begin to affect reaction efficiency **before major system failure**, making this a potentially useful early indicator.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 5. Vibration as a Key Fault Indicator\n",
