    "## 18. Transition to Feature Engineering\n",
    "\n",
    "The exploratory analysis has revealed critical patterns in the dataset, including regime-dependent behavior, strong mechanical fault signals, temporal clustering of faults, and multivariate interactions between key process variables.\n",
    "\n",
    "While these insights provide a deep understanding of the system, they must now be translated into **structured, model-ready features**.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why Feature Engineering is Necessary\n",
    "\n",
    "Raw sensor data, although informative, does not fully capture:\n",
    "\n",
    "- temporal dependencies (what happens *before* a fault)\n",
    "- variability and instability patterns\n",
    "- regime-specific deviations\n",
    "- interaction effects between variables\n",
    "\n",
    "> To build effective predictive models, we must convert raw signals into **meaningful representations of system behavior**.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Learnings Driving Feature Engineering\n",
    "\n",
    "From the exploratory analysis, we identified that:\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1. Faults are preceded by instability\n",
    "- Increased variability (not just mean shifts)\n",
    "- Sudden spikes (especially in vibration)\n",
    "\n",
    "We need features that capture:\n",
    "- rolling statistics (mean, std)\n",
    "- rate of change\n",
    "- volatility\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 2. Mechanical signals are early indicators\n",
    "- Vibration shows strong separation\n",
    "- Likely precedes performance degradation\n",
    "\n",
    "We need:\n",
    "- lag features\n",
    "- spike detection features\n",
    "- trend-based indicators\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 3. System behavior depends on operating regime\n",
    "- Different baselines for regime A vs B\n",
    "\n",
    "We need:\n",
    "- regime-aware normalization\n",
    "- deviation-from-regime features\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 4. Temporal structure is critical\n",
    "- Faults cluster over time\n",
    "- System alternates between stable and unstable states\n",
    "\n",
    "We need:\n",
    "- time-based features\n",
    "- rolling fault counts\n",
    "- historical context variables\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 5. Multivariate relationships matter\n",
    "- Some faults only appear through variable interactions\n",
    "\n",
    "We need:\n",
    "- interaction features (e.g., temp × pressure)\n",
    "- combined indicators\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Feature Engineering Objectives\n",
    "\n",
    "The goal is to create features that allow models to:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Detect early warning signals  \n",
    "2. Capture system instability  \n",
    "3. Understand operating context  \n",
    "4. Distinguish between normal variation and true faults  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Categories of Features to Be Created\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 1. Statistical Features\n",
    "- rolling mean\n",
    "- rolling standard deviation\n",
    "- min / max over time windows\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 2. Temporal Features\n",
    "- lagged variables (t-1, t-5, t-10)\n",
    "- rate of change (Δ values)\n",
    "- trend indicators\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 3. Regime-Based Features\n",
    "- deviation from regime mean\n",
    "- normalized variables per regime\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 4. Interaction Features\n",
    "- temperature × pressure\n",
    "- vibration × power\n",
    "- derived ratios\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 5. Fault History Features\n",
    "- rolling fault counts\n",
    "- time since last fault\n",
    "- recent fault density\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 6. Anomaly Indicators\n",
    "- z-scores\n",
    "- threshold-based flags\n",
    "- spike detection features\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Expected Impact\n",
    "\n",
    "By engineering these features, we aim to:\n",
    "\n",
    "- improve model accuracy\n",
    "- enhance early fault detection capability\n",
    "- reduce false positives\n",
    "- capture hidden system dynamics\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Transition to Implementation\n",
    "\n",
    "We now move from **understanding the system** to **building predictive intelligence**.\n",
    "\n",
    "> The next section focuses on constructing these engineered features step by step, starting with temporal and statistical transformations."
   ]
